<br>
You need to do 25% or more damage, otherwise the pet takes 50%.  I think this is only with CHARMED pets of course, not regular summoned.  I've heard they'll take 75% XP too, but I'm not sure.  Charm kiting in PoN for 7 levels I noticed theres a huge difference in how much XP you get depending on if you do the major damage or the pet.  The key is to camo/invis and dispell charm before the mob dies, and kill off your pet and your opponent.  Then you get full XP for both.<br>
<br>
Otherwise let you pet kill one mob, don't heal it up, move on to the next and try to get them both as close to 15% or so as possible, then break charm and kill them.  This is usually the most efficient way of doing it and worked incredible in PoN.  But, it totally depends on what level you are, what class, and how you can handle adds etc. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#660066><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub22.ezboard.com/brutabagaparadoxforum.showUserPublicProfile?gid=konst>Konst</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I Found The Salad Bar! </span><br>  Posts: 34<br> <font color=#FFFF00>(9/18/03 8:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p066.ezboard.com/frutabagaparadoxforumgeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1398.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m colspan=2><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_mad.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Charming Exp Nerf?</span><hr size=1> I went from getting 4% AA per charmed kill in PoN, to getting 2% AA per charmed kill. Both times I never did any damage myself. I'm told if you do more than 50% of the dmg (Or the group does more than 50% of the dmg) it does not take any exp. That has been what I've noticed in PoP. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=46378&amp;resize=true">Matife Danzabbar</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
